{
  "texts": [
    "As Fig 3 shows, the SDK operates the hardware either through the kernel driver (safe mode) or directly from the user space (performance mode).",
    "In safe mode, operations are done through ioctls sent to the driver, providing isolation between host applications.",
    "In performance mode, the host application mmaps the whole MRAMs and control interfaces, allowing it to bypass the driver completely.",
    "vPIM uses both modes for different purposes.UPMEM Hardware Limitations.",
    "UPMEM has the following three limitations which pose challenges for virtualization."
